cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.SI 

This paper deals with natural language processing and machine learning techniques to detect causal relationships between time series events and textual data. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper involves the use of neural networks and reasoning algorithms, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves information retrieval techniques to extract features from text, which falls under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper deals with commonsense knowledge and reasoning, which is relevant to the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
